                                @Required
                              ---------------
>It removed from Spring(5.x)...
>It work only on method level..
>It given for setter type property for mandatory injection,that mean if we write @Required at top of
 setter method then that method type property value must be injected otherwise..it throw error..
 >If class have 4 setter method and we configured @Required for only two method then that configured 2 method 
  is mandatory for injection and other 2 method is not mandatory...
 >While working with annotation we can"t work lambok api... 